#!/usr/bin/env bash
# License: GPLv3
# Credits: Felipe Facundes (original), enhanced version

: <<'DOCUMENTATION'
1. Terminal Bible reader with dialog UI and SQLite database.
2. Supports multiple Bible translations (auto-detected .sqlite files).
3. Downloads Bibles from https://github.com/felipefacundes/biblias via git clone.
4. Navigate 66 books, chapters and verses with last-read history.
5. Global search (whole Bible) or per-book search.
6. Highlight search terms with customizable colors ("-d", "-w", "-b").
7. Search modes: "F" toggles between case-sensitive and case-insensitive.
8. Quick navigation: "w/s", "j/k" or arrows, "/" search, "n/N" between matches.
9. Translation comparator: view the same verse across all available Bibles.
10. i18n support: Portuguese and English (auto-detected from $LANG).
-- ENHANCEMENTS --
11. Direct verse navigation: type "Book Chapter:Verse" (e.g., John 3:16).
12. Favorite individual verses (in addition to whole chapters).
13. Export translation comparison to text or PDF.
14. Filter translations in comparison view.
15. Continuous reading mode: auto-advance chapters.
16. Verse numbers highlighted in a distinct color from text.
17. Regex search support (in addition to LIKE).
18. Translation statistics (book count, verse count, etc.).
DOCUMENTATION

